title.narrative: Output 3.2: Increased number of communities in targeted counties, that demonstrate a rejection of harmful practices such as child marriage and FGM/C

description.narrative: In line with the national gender-based violence strategic plan (2018-2022) the female genital mutilation and child marriage programmes continue to strengthen coordination and response. Standardized quality services have been provided to 982 girls at risk of FGM or those who have undergone FGM specifically in 6 out of 11 sub- counties (55%); 16 communities pledged to abandon FGM. The programme reached 86,346 persons (48,259 female and 38,087 male) which supported identification and provision of services to 3,500 girls at risks of FGM and 116 girls at risk of child marriage. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
